   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Expense Category Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes organizational expense data by category, team, vendor, and time period to highlight overspending areas, seasonality, and cost anomalies.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Categorize and visualize expense patterns across an organization.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify top spending categories and vendors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Detect expense anomalies and seasonal patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Generate cost optimization recommendations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Organizations often lack visibility into where money is being spent. Expense analysis reveals hidden costs, budget overruns, and optimization opportunities.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Cutting unnecessary expenses by 5-10% can significantly improve profitability without impacting operations.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **6,000 expense records** over 12 months across multiple departments.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 6000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CATEGORIES = [\\\"Travel\\\", \\\"Software\\\", \\\"Office Supplies\\\", \\\"Marketing\\\", \\\"Consulting\\\", \\\"Equipment\\\", \\\"Training\\\", \\\"Utilities\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DEPARTMENTS = [\\\"Engineering\\\", \\\"Sales\\\", \\\"Marketing\\\", \\\"HR\\\", \\\"Finance\\\", \\\"Operations\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"VENDORS = [f\\\"Vendor_{chr(65+i)}\\\" for i in range(15)]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cat_avgs = {\\\"Travel\\\": 800, \\\"Software\\\": 500, \\\"Office Supplies\\\": 60, \\\"Marketing\\\": 2000,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"Consulting\\\": 3000, \\\"Equipment\\\": 1200, \\\"Training\\\": 400, \\\"Utilities\\\": 300}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cat = rng.choice(CATEGORIES, p=[0.15,0.15,0.12,0.15,0.10,0.12,0.10,0.11])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    dept = rng.choice(DEPARTMENTS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    vendor = rng.choice(VENDORS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    amount = max(5, round(rng.exponential(cat_avgs[cat]), 2))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    date = rng.choice(dates)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\\"expense_id\\\": f\\\"EXP{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"date\\\": date, \\\"category\\\": cat,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                 \\\"department\\\": dept, \\\"vendor\\\": vendor, \\\"amount\\\": amount})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"quarter\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.quarter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Total spend: ${df['amount'].sum():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}, ✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"category\\\")[\\\"amount\\\"].sum().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0,0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,0].set_title(\\\"Total Spend by Category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"department\\\")[\\\"amount\\\"].sum().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0,1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,1].set_title(\\\"Total Spend by Department\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"monthly = df.groupby(\\\"month\\\")[\\\"amount\\\"].sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].plot(monthly.index, monthly.values, marker=\\\"o\\\", color=\\\"seagreen\\\", linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].set_title(\\\"Monthly Total Spend\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].set_xlabel(\\\"Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top_vendors = df.groupby(\\\"vendor\\\")[\\\"amount\\\"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top_vendors.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1,1], color=\\\"purple\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_title(\\\"Top 10 Vendors by Spend\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Category × Department heatmap\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pivot = df.pivot_table(values=\\\"amount\\\", index=\\\"department\\\", columns=\\\"category\\\", aggfunc=\\\"sum\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(pivot, annot=True, fmt=\\\",.0f\\\", cmap=\\\"YlOrRd\\\", ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Spend Heatmap: Department × Category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Anomaly detection: expenses > 3 std from category mean\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cat_stats = df.groupby(\\\"category\\\")[\\\"amount\\\"].agg([\\\"mean\\\", \\\"std\\\"]).reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df_check = df.merge(cat_stats, on=\\\"category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df_check[\\\"z_score\\\"] = (df_check[\\\"amount\\\"] - df_check[\\\"mean\\\"]) / df_check[\\\"std\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"anomalies = df_check[df_check[\\\"z_score\\\"] > 3]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Potential anomalies (z > 3): {len(anomalies)} out of {len(df)} expenses\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if len(anomalies) > 0:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(anomalies[[\\\"expense_id\\\",\\\"category\\\",\\\"department\\\",\\\"amount\\\",\\\"z_score\\\"]].head(10))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Consulting and Marketing are the largest spend categories** — these should be reviewed for ROI.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Vendor concentration exists** — a few vendors capture a disproportionate share of spend.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Monthly spend shows some seasonal variation** worth monitoring.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Several expense anomalies detected** — these warrant manual review.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data without real budget context.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No approval workflow data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No multi-year comparison.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Negotiate volume discounts with top vendors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Set category-level budgets and track variance.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Review anomalous expenses for policy compliance.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Consolidate vendors to improve negotiating leverage.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Cutting costs uniformly instead of targeting low-ROI categories.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Not comparing spend to business outcomes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Ignoring small, frequent expenses that add up.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Not adjusting for seasonality when comparing periods.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build a monthly budget vs actual comparison.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Create a Pareto chart showing which categories account for 80% of spend.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Identify departments with the highest per-capita spending.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Expense visibility is the first step to cost optimization.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Category and vendor analysis reveals concentration risks.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Anomaly detection flags potential policy violations or errors.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
